    ],
    "summary": "On September 24, 2014, approximately 150 barrels of Synthetic Based Mud (SBM) were discharged into the Gulf of Mexico from the Noble Driller while crews prepared the rig for well completion. A leaking dump valve on mud pit #3, combined with open master valves from ongoing cleaning operations and an inoperable Pit Volume Transmitter alarm, resulted in undetected fluid loss over approximately 1.5 hours.",
